709116f-a.text:
Pifth Ave., east side, south from (No. 854) a point midway between East 67th and 66th Streets and across the latter to 65th Street, showing 3 structures and a vacant lot occupying this area. From left to right these are: the home of Emily V. White, No. 854; the former site of the Havermeyer homes (N.E. corner of 66th Street); an 11-story apartment house, No. 845 Fifth Ave., (at the e.E. corner of 66th Street) and the Temple Emanu-El Congregation of New York at the N.E. corner of 65th Street. The latter occupies the site of the former John J. Astor home.
July 21, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
